rsee covert activity and propose guidelines for political leaders who may contemplate using covert techniques. An appendix reviews twenty years of allegations of covert aggression brought to the attention of the United Nations Security Council.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016063540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300160635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300160635/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles